message.content: For a certain number of oranges $n$ at $3x$ cents each, Kim's supply of money is $40\cdot3x=120x$ cents. Because she had exactly enough money to buy these 40 oranges, $n$ satisfies $\frac{120x}{n}=3x$, or $n=40$. However, if she now wishes to buy the same number of $n$ oranges at $4x$ cents each, she must have $40\cdot4x=160x$ cents. So, Kim can buy $\boxed{40}$ oranges.
